{
  "doc_id": "9891",
  "text": "Osteonecrosis (ON) is a disease resulting from temporary or permanent loss of blood supply to the bones. The most common causes of ON are; trauma, drugs, infections, hypercoagulable conditions and solid organ transplantation. [CITATION_1] Osteonecrosis has been reported in many case series after renal, liver and cardiac transplantation; mainly in areas adjacent to the joints, especially on hip. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] Here, we are reporting multifocal ON with osteomyelitis including diaphyseal region of the tibia in a patient with liver transplantation.",
